ih (authentic) according to Muslim \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a \u0647\u064f\u0631\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0631\u064e\u0629\u064e\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":23708,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2016\/09\/10\/sins-expiate-ruku-sujud\/","url_meta":{"origin":34450,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Salat: Sins fall away as they bow, prostrate","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"September 10, 2016","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Umar reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cVerily, when a servant stands to pray, his sins are placed on top of his head and shoulders. Every time he bows or prostrates, they fall away from him.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Ibn H\u0323ibba\u0304n 1734 Grade: Sahih\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":36258,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/05\/21\/hasanat-expiates-past-sins\/","url_meta":{"origin":34450,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Tawbah: Good deeds expiate past sins in life","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 21, 2021","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Dharr reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhoever does good in what remains of his life, he will be forgiven for what has passed. Whoever does evil in what remains of his life, he will be taken to account for what has passed\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quo